The structure of this dataset¶

The dataset has 113937 rows and 81 columns, for our analysis we need just 12 of them (ListingKey,Term,LoanStatus,LoanOriginalAmount,EstimatedReturn,ProsperScore,DelinquenciesLast7Years,DebtToIncomeRatio,IncomeRange,IncomeVerifiable,PercentFunded,Investors), most of the data are numeric except income rage and income verifiable, prosper score is numeric but it's a categoriacal data representing the estimated risk of the loan

What is the main feature of interest in this dataset?¶

I’m interested to find out what can influence the percentage of funding the loan got and the number of investors invested on the loan

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I'm expecting that the DelinquenciesLast7Years, ProsperScore, and EstimatedReturn will have the most impact on the percentage of funding and the number of investors

loan['IncomeRange']=loan['IncomeRange'].astype(incrang)

2. On this part we will the relation between the estimated return, LoanOriginalAmount, DelinquenciesLast7Years and DebtToIncomeRatio with the number of investors¶

In [25]:
def scatter(data,x,y,til):
  plt.figure(figsize = [10, 8])
  plt.scatter(data =data , x = x, y = y, alpha=2/20)
  plt.xlabel(x)
  plt.ylabel(y)
  plt.title(til)
  plt.show()
    
def scatterlx(data,x,y,til):
  plt.figure(figsize = [10, 8])
  plt.scatter(data =data , x = x, y = y, alpha=2/20)
  plt.xscale('log')
  plt.xlabel(x)
  plt.ylabel(y)
  plt.title(til)
  plt.show()
    
def scatterly(data,x,y,til):
  plt.figure(figsize = [10, 8])
  plt.scatter(data =data , x = x, y = y, alpha=2/20)
  plt.xlabel(x)
  plt.ylabel(y)
  plt.yscale('log')
  plt.title(til)
  plt.show()

def Mscatter(data,x,y,c,til,lim):
  plt.figure(figsize = [10, 8])
  g = sb.FacetGrid(data = data, hue = c, height = 5, palette='viridis')
  g.map(plt.scatter, x, y,alpha  = 0.5)
  g.add_legend()
  plt.xlim(lim)
  plt.title(til)
  plt.show()

Talk about some of the relation you observed in this part of the investigation. Were there features that strengthened each other in terms of looking at your feature(s) of interest?¶

I found that investors are more interested in loans with low Estimated returns but in the same time they have a low risk, the seconde observation I found that there is a positive relation between the income range and the prosper risk that means that the higher the income range the lower is the risk. finally i found that the higher the income range the lower the delinquencies is.

Conclusions¶

I choosed the Loan dataset to answer the questions about what impact the percentage funded of the loan and the number of investors. Unfortunately the majority of loans was 100% funded that prented us to find any correlation between the percentFunded and the other variables. In other side the number of investors was more exploitable. we found some positive relations with the income range, the prosper risk, and the original amount of the loan as expected.
